# CCNA LAB 05 — EtherChannel Mismatch Catastrophe

## Objective

Build an EtherChannel between two switches and intentionally create a negotiation mismatch.

Test:

* PAgP mismatch behavior
* STP instability
* Link flapping
* Syslog error messages
* Traffic impact

Then fix the issue using:

* Proper LACP configuration
* Consistent channel-group settings

This lab demonstrates one of the most common Layer 2 misconfigurations in enterprise networks.

