# STEP 2 — CONFIGURE BROKEN ETHERCHANNEL

# Intentional mismatch:

# SW1 = PAgP desirable

# SW2 = mode on

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## SW1

```cisco id="v9l0u3"
configure terminal

interface range g0/1 - 2
 channel-group 1 mode desirable

interface port-channel 1
 switchport trunk encapsulation dot1q
 switchport mode trunk

end
write memory
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## SW2

```cisco id="h8x3g0"
configure terminal

interface range g0/1 - 2
 channel-group 1 mode on

interface port-channel 1
 switchport trunk encapsulation dot1q
 switchport mode trunk

end
write memory
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# EXPECTED FAILURE

The EtherChannel modes do NOT match.

Result:

* Channel instability
* Links may individually forward
* STP detects inconsistent topology
* MAC flapping possible

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

