# REAL-WORLD IMPORTANCE

Bad EtherChannel configs can cause:

* MAC flapping
* Broadcast storms
* STP instability
* Intermittent outages
* Random packet drops

This is one of the most common enterprise switching issues during:

* Migration projects
* New uplink deployment
* Data center expansion

